.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  ! GF I think this next select is a problem, it should select trans_user_id &
trans_sys_dt based on the trans_id_cred & dt instead. Is it backwards?
.head 7 -  ! GF 17/11/99 I tnink I have been wrong all along, as invoiceing used to work, if there was an invoice
worth less than a deposit, the invoice would be a credit invoice (make sense of that if you can) and then
there probably was another invoice that also could be attached to the deposit, therefor we needed to 
get that invoice to see if there was any balance and if there was don't roll any of it.
Thsi has made it hard as now that we no longer have credit invoices, how do we stop things rolling if there
is any related stuff with a non zero balance.
